sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User (Browser)
    participant FE as Frontend (React)
    participant API as Backend (Express)
    participant AN as Analyzer Engine
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant GH as GitHub API

    U->>FE: Select source type & input
    
    alt GitHub Source
        FE->>API: POST /api/fetch-skill {source, sourceType: "github"}
        API->>GH: GET /repos/{owner}/{repo}/git/trees
        GH-->>API: Repository tree
        API->>GH: GET /repos/{owner}/{repo}/contents/{path}
        GH-->>API: Raw file contents
        API-->>FE: {code: "..."}
    else URL Source
        FE->>API: POST /api/fetch-skill {source, sourceType: "url"}
        API->>API: fetch(source URL)
        API-->>FE: {code: "..."}
    else Paste/Local
        Note over FE: Code already available client-side
    end

    FE->>FE: Show AnalysisSim animation
    FE->>API: POST /api/evaluate {source, sourceType, code}
    API->>AN: analyzeCode(code)
    
    Note over AN: Pattern Matching Phase
    AN->>AN: Check dangerous patterns (eval, exec, __proto__)
    AN->>AN: Check secret patterns (API keys, tokens)
    AN->>AN: Check quality patterns (empty catch, console.log)
    AN->>AN: Run heuristic checks (length, comments, types)
    AN->>AN: Calculate scores (Safety 40%, Security 30%, Quality 30%)
    AN-->>API: {scores, findings, summary}

    API->>DB: INSERT INTO evaluations
    DB-->>API: Evaluation record
    API-->>FE: Evaluation JSON response

    FE->>FE: Transition to EvaluationReport
    FE->>U: Display scores, findings, download option
